Headlines.Author: Robbie Whelan
Headlines.Headline: What You Need to Know About Nontraded REITs

PARAGRAPH.#text: State securities regulators are stepping up scrutiny of nontraded real-estate investment trusts, a type of real-estate fund that has grown rapidly in popularity since the real-estate crash.Nontraded REITs have been in the news a lot lately, partly because of their growth—and partly because regulators including the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority and the Securities and Exchange Commission have taken notice in recent years, after a spate of bad press related to some nontraded REITs that turned out to be big losers for investors.So what's all the fuss about? Here are answers to five key questions.

PARAGRAPH.#text: Public Storage's PSA third-quarter profit rose 7.7% on the strength of higher occupancy and rents. Headlines.Author: Kristin Jones
Headlines.Headline: Public Storage 2nd-Quarter Profit Flat; Rental Revenue Improves

PARAGRAPH.#text: Public Storage's PSA second-quarter profit was roughly flat from a year ago as rental revenue improved, offset by currency exchange impacts. Public Storage, which owns storage facilities and operates as a real-estate investment trust, has benefited from industry consolidation, giving it an advertising advantage and allowing it to gain market share. Still, the company's results have been mixed in recent quarters, as expenses have sometimes outpaced revenue growth. The company posted a profit of $205.9 million, or 73 cents a share, down from $206.1 million, or 87 cents a share, a year earlier.

Headlines.Headline: Public Storage CEO Havner Succeeds Company Founder Hughes As Chairman

PARAGRAPH.#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Public Storage's PSA board elected Chief Executive Ronald L. Havner Jr. as its chairman as well, succeeding the storage-facility company's founder, B. Wayne Hughes. Havner, 53, succeeded Hughes as chief executive in 2002, after serving in several management positions since he joined the company in 1986. Hughes, 77, has been a member of the board since its organization in 1980 and will remain a trustee of the company. A release from Public Storage on Tuesday said Hughes currently operates a horse farm in Kentucky.

Headlines.Headline: Public Storage 2Q Up 61% on Higher Occupancy, Year-Ago Loss

PARAGRAPH.#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Public Storage Inc.'s PSA second-quarter earnings grew 61% on higher occupancy and rents, as well as a foreign-exchange loss in the prior period, while a key profitability metric for the real-estate investment trust improved. The storage facility has seen funds from operations, a key profitability metric, rise in recent quarters as revenue also increased. Bank of America Merrill Lynch, which raised its stock-investment rating on the company in June, said Public Storage stands to gain due to a strong move towards consolidation as smaller operators lack scale to advertise effectively.
